# Zing - Cursor Rules
# Receptionist & Dispatch Call Routing App for Small Business

## Project Overview
Zing is a VoIP call routing app that lets small business owners manage who answers their business calls. Think Grasshopper/RingCentral but radically simpler. The UI is fully built in Next.js -- your job is to wire it to real backend services and optionally port the frontend to React Native/Expo for mobile.

## Tech Stack
- **Frontend**: Next.js 16, React 19, TailwindCSS v4, shadcn/ui
- **Backend**: Next.js API routes (already scaffolded)
- **Database**: Postgres via Supabase or Neon (schema in scripts/001-create-schema.sql)
- **Telephony**: Twilio or Telnyx (voice, numbers, recordings). Telnyx is the preferred provider; use /api/voice/telnyx/* and /api/numbers/telnyx for new setup.
- **AI**: Vercel AI SDK v6 for AI receptionist fallback
- **Auth**: Supabase Auth or custom (bcrypt + HTTP-only cookies)

## Architecture

### How Call Routing Works
1. Caller dials the business Twilio number
2. Twilio hits POST /api/voice/incoming
3. Server checks routing_config for this user
4. If receptionist selected: Dial receptionist with timeout
5. If no answer: POST /api/voice/fallback checks fallback_type
   - "owner" -> Dial owner's cell
   - "ai" -> Connect to AI assistant
   - "voicemail" -> Play greeting + record
6. POST /api/voice/status logs final call data

### Database Schema (scripts/001-create-schema.sql)
- users: business owners
- receptionists: agents who answer calls, each has rate_per_minute
- routing_config: who receives calls + fallback settings (one row per user)
- phone_numbers: Twilio numbers owned/ported
- call_logs: every call with duration, recording URL, who it was routed to

### Shared Types (lib/types.ts)
All TypeScript interfaces for the database models and API request/response shapes.

### Database Client (lib/db.ts)
Placeholder query functions. Every function has the correct signature and return type -- implement with your DB provider's client.

### Twilio Client (lib/twilio.ts)
REST client factory, webhook validator, TwiML builder, and app URL helper.

## App Screens (components/)
| File | Screen | Purpose |
|------|--------|---------|
| dashboard-page.tsx | Routing | Main screen. Shows who calls route to. Tap name to switch. Fallback settings (owner/AI/voicemail). Call stats + recent calls. |
| activity-page.tsx | Activity | Full call log with search, filters, expandable rows, inline audio player for recordings. |
| contacts-page.tsx | Contacts | Manage receptionists. Add/remove/toggle/prioritize. |
| analytics-page.tsx | Pay | Per-agent talk time tracking. Configurable $/min rate. Auto-calculated weekly earnings. Payout summary. |
| settings-page.tsx | Settings | DND, voicemail, business hours, SMS forwarding, push notifications. Buy/port phone numbers. |
| app-shell.tsx | Shell | Bottom tab navigation + header. Accepts activePage prop. |

## API Routes (app/api/)
| Route | Method | Purpose |
|-------|--------|---------|
| /api/voice/incoming | POST | Twilio webhook: routes incoming calls |
| /api/voice/fallback | POST | Twilio webhook: handles no-answer fallback |
| /api/voice/status | POST | Twilio webhook: logs call completion data |
| /api/voice/recording-status | POST | Twilio webhook: attaches recording URLs |
| /api/voice/ai-assistant | POST | Twilio webhook: AI answers + converses with caller |
| /api/routing | GET/PUT | Read/update routing config |
| /api/calls | GET | Paginated call history |
| /api/numbers | GET/POST | List owned numbers / search available |
| /api/numbers/buy | POST | Purchase a Twilio number |
| /api/numbers/telnyx | GET | Search available Telnyx numbers (query: area_code, type) |
| /api/numbers/telnyx/buy | POST | Purchase a Telnyx number (body: { phone_number }) |
| /api/voice/telnyx/incoming | GET/POST | Telnyx TeXML: route incoming calls |
| /api/voice/telnyx/fallback | POST | Telnyx: no-answer fallback |
| /api/voice/telnyx/status | POST | Telnyx: call status callback |
| /api/voice/telnyx/recording-status | POST | Telnyx: recording callback |
| /api/voice/telnyx/ai-assistant | POST | Telnyx: AI receptionist |
| /api/numbers/port | POST | Submit a port request |
| /api/analytics | GET | Agent talk time + pay calculations |

## Environment Variables Required
```
# Database (pick one)
DATABASE_URL=                           # Neon
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=               # Supabase
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=              # Supabase

# Twilio (optional if using Telnyx)
TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=
TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=

# Telnyx (preferred for new setups)
TELNYX_API_KEY=                        # REST API + TeXML
TELNYX_PUBLIC_KEY=                     # Optional: webhook signature verification
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=                   # Your deployed URL (for webhook URLs)

# AI (for AI receptionist fallback)
OPENAI_API_KEY=                         # Or use Vercel AI Gateway
```

## Implementation Order
1. Connect database (Supabase or Neon) - implement lib/db.ts functions
2. Add authentication (Supabase Auth or custom)
3. Wire UI components to real API routes (replace useState with SWR/fetch)
4. Set up Twilio account + buy first number
5. Configure Twilio webhooks to point to /api/voice/incoming
6. Test call routing flow end-to-end
7. Implement AI assistant fallback
8. Add push notifications for missed calls

## Coding Conventions
- Use `async/await` for all DB and API calls
- Validate all Twilio webhooks with `validateTwilioRequest()`
- Use parameterized queries only (never string interpolation for SQL)
- All API routes return JSON with `{ data }` or `{ error }` shape
- Phone numbers stored in E.164 format (+15551234567) internally
- UI uses semantic Tailwind tokens (bg-card, text-foreground, etc.)
- Components use cn() from lib/utils for conditional classes

## Mobile (React Native / Expo)
If porting to mobile:
- Each *-page.tsx maps 1:1 to a tab screen
- app-shell.tsx bottom nav -> Expo Router tabs or React Navigation BottomTabNavigator
- Replace shadcn components with React Native equivalents (react-native-paper, nativewind)
- API routes stay as-is on the Next.js backend
- Mobile app calls the same /api/* endpoints
